<div id="review_123580496" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/123580496" />
    <a title="Bob Caroti" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2433503-bob-caroti"><img alt="Bob Caroti" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/123580496?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bob Caroti" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bob Caroti" href="/user/show/2433503-bob-caroti">Bob Caroti</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer123580496" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12747429045561543068">I had to have knee surgery this past spring and was looking for something to get me thru being homebound for awhile. I found the &apos;Camulod Chronicles&apos; that began with &apos;The Skystone&apos; and has progressed thru this book ... The premise fasinated me ... What happened in Britain between the time the Roman Legions left and when King Arthur and his Knights of the Round Table evolved and ruled? Where did Arthur and Merlyn come from? What was so special about the sword &apos;Excalibur&apos;? How did the church becom</span>
  <span id="freeText12747429045561543068" style="display:none">I had to have knee surgery this past spring and was looking for something to get me thru being homebound for awhile. I found the 'Camulod Chronicles' that began with 'The Skystone' and has progressed thru this book ... The premise fasinated me ... What happened in Britain between the time the Roman Legions left and when King Arthur and his Knights of the Round Table evolved and ruled? Where did Arthur and Merlyn come from? What was so special about the sword 'Excalibur'? How did the church become the dominate force of the middle ages? Jack Whyte weaves a wonderful (but gritty) tale that is well worth the effort. I see there are 3 more volumns to this series and will continue but I think he could have stopped with 'The Sorcerer' and left people happy. I think many of you would enjoy this series ... Loved it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12747429045561543068" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


